                        <td width="72%" valign="top">
                            <h2>
                                Welcome to Big River Kayaking!</h2>
                            <p>
                                Big River Kayaking was founded in 1998 with the goal of teaching the right kayaking
                                in a safe and fun environment. Our certified instructors will teach you the basics
                                of kayaking, including proper techniques and everything else you need to know to
                                be safe and feel comfortable paddling a kayak. After introducing you to the sport
                                of kayaking and to your equipment, you will get your first taste of paddling in
                                the security of a lake or canal. You will learn basic safety and rules of the water,
                                the different types of boats, their parts, and proper fit. You will also learn how
                                to get in and out of a kayak, how to do a wet exit in the event of a capsize, how
                                to do a partner assisted T-rescue, and the basic paddle stroke techniques: turning,
                                stopping, spinning and going straight, forward and reverse.</p>
                            <p>
                                Once you are comfortable with the basics, you will head to moving water where you
                                will learn intermediate techniques including hip snap development, which means controlling
                                your boat with your body, and self rescue techniques such as paddle float and cowboy
                                rescue. Students with a solid grasp of basic and intermediate techniques will learn
                                advanced rescue techniques, how to paddle in waves above three feet, roll theory,
                                and advanced paddle strokes such as side slip, towing, sprint paddling.</p>
